Name: Description
Median Monthly Rent: Median contract (or asking) rent for rental households.

Name: Source Notes
Median Monthly Rent: U.S. Census Bureau, American Community Survey 1-Year Estimates, Table B25058 (2005-2017); retrieved from https://data.census.gov/.

Name: Notes
Median Monthly Rent:
Dollar amounts for all years adjusted to constant 2018 dollars using the Consumer Price Index Research Series Using Current Methods (CPI-U-RS) for all items; retrieved from https://www.bls.gov/cpi/research-series/home.htm. 
Some of the median rents reported by the Census have been "top-coded" into the highest standard deviation category; instances that fall into this category have been labeled as "Topcoded." The topcoded amount for median rent is $2,000 (in current year dollars). Due to adjustment for inflation, some rents displayed for prior years may exceed the topcoded amount.
